This is a stripped down version of cltwitter only using the single
access token method of authenticating.
http://dev.twitter.com/pages/oauth_single_token

DEPENDENCIES)
=============
 - libcurl (http://curl.haxx.se)
 - liboauth (http://liboauth.sourceforge.net)
 
INSTALLATION)
=============
*NIX:
  $ ./autogen.sh
  $ ./configure
  $ make
  # make install


CONFIGURATION)
==============
Before compilation, go to http://dev.twitter.com/
and get the info to set OAUTH_CONSUMER_KEY, OAUTH_CONSUMER_SECRET,
OAUTH_TOKEN and OAUTH_TOKEN_SECRET in definitions.h


USAGE)
======

Supplying Twitter message on the command line:

  $ tweet "Hello Twitter!"

NOTES)
======
As usual the tweets must be 1-140 characters long. 

HAPPY TWEETING!
